HEADWORD: Wringbolt
<hw>Wring"bolt`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>A
bolt used by shipwrights, to bend and secure the planks against the
timbers till they are fastened by bolts, spikes, or treenails; -- not to
be confounded with <xex>ringbolt</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wringer</ent>⟦br⟧
